{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the data indicates that the GA with diversity not only identifies regions within the search space that contribute to higher execution times-implying a more accurate estimation of the WCET-but also ensures a more comprehensive examination of possible scenarios, enhancing the reliability of the results.",
    "RandGA Exec GA Exec Div In addition, Figures 5.2a and 5.2b show the maximum execution time fitness score of the GA during the algorithm's run.",
    "These figures show how the diversity fitness function changes the algorithm's behavior.",
    "In the first scenario, where only execution time is used as a fitness function, the progression of execution times across generations shows relatively moderate fluctuations.",
    "This trend suggests a focused exploration within a narrower solution space, possibly converging towards local optima without thoroughly exploring the breadth of possible solutions."
  ]
}